      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with elastic-plastic material model and frictional contact is appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending of metallic implant constructs.",
      "rationale": "The continuum FEA approach with isotropic hardening plasticity and frictional contact (mu=0.2) is well-established for metallic spinal implant constructs under quasi-static loading. Geometric nonlinearity is included to capture large-displacement effects at 40 mm displacement. Model form is consistent with published literature and FDA guidance."
