    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 is accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed the required credibility level for Medium model risk. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on the conservative and standardized nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and supporting clinical performance evidence. All three pre-specified QoIs pass quantitative acceptance bounds with E/uval values well below 1.96. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the intended use of supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
